ly estimated.  Good communication with the ship and planning allowed for the slight increase.  While we did end up consuming 90mt of gasoil, the difference was only $6k more compared to vlsfo.  We also saved time and port costs not having to bunker in South Africa enroute.  Doing so was the most commercially viable option given her intake limitations to meet draft restrictions at the disport.\nImprovements:  Having to trouble shoot with Orbit regarding daily report exclusions.  As such will update new voyage report once issue has been solved.\n\nFixture Notes:   We say good bye to our Alcoa COA to Australia with this last lift loading Houston to Kwinana. Meeting expectations in TCE adjusted to the BAF of $1,280 per USD increase in price above $315/pmt. Wonderful voyage indeed and thanks to Alcoa for this little COA.\n\n\n\nVessel                                LARGO ENERGY #2109\nCharterers                        Alcoa Steamship.                         \nCP date                             17TH Nov, 2020                               \nBroker                               Kim Elbaek - Netco                                 \nOperator                          Jason Eisemann                            \nCargo                                CSS                           \nLoad                                  HOUSTON  \nDischarge                         KWINANA  \nLay can                             20-30 December    \nRate                                  $38pmt\nTCE                                    $17,230/day   \nDemurrage                      $19,000/day\nExpected result              $130,500 overall basis $14,800/day hire. \nVoyage days                    55 DAYS"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-03-02T00:37:59.003","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"Increase of TCE due to BROB at arrival Kwinana more than VMS estimated for."},{"modifiedDate":"2022-01-05T03:50:49.753","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"Cls 10.7 mentions if arriving after laycan time not to count until all fast.  As there is berthing delays this greatly affects results.  Are seeking legal interpitation if cls 5.5 can assist."}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}